		fDocs.put("xdmp:save","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:save(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">path as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">node as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[options as node()?]</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Serializes a node as text and saves it to a file. The node can be any node, including a document node, an element node, a text node, or a binary node. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:save\">Complete Information for xdmp:save</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:document-load","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:document-load(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">location as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[options as node()?]</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Inserts a new document with the specified URI. If a document already exists at the URI, the function replaces the content in the existing document as an update operation. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:document-load\">Complete Information for xdmp:document-load</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:load","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:load(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">path as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[uri as xs:string?,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[permissions as element(sec:permission)*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[collections as xs:string*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[quality as xs:int?,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[default-namespace as xs:string?,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[options as xs:string*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[forest-ids as xs:unsignedLong*]</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> [DEPRECATED: use <a href=\"#document-load\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><code>xdmp:document-load</code></a> instead] Inserts a new document from the XML file at $path if a document with the specified URI does not already exist. Otherwise, the function replaces the content in the existing document as an update operation. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:load\">Complete Information for xdmp:load</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:document-insert","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:document-insert(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">root as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[permissions as element(sec:permission)*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[collections as xs:string*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[quality as xs:int?,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[forest-ids as xs:unsignedLong*]</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Inserts a new document into the database if a document with the specified URI does not already exist. If a document already exists at the specified URI, the function replaces the content of the existing document with the specified content (the <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">$root</code> parameter) as an update operation. In addition to replacing the content, <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">xdmp:document-insert</code> replaces any permissions, collections, and quality with the ones specified (or with the default values for these parameters, if not explicitly specified). Also, if a properties document exists at the same URI, that properties document (including any content it contains) is preserved. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:document-insert\">Complete Information for xdmp:document-insert</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:directory-create","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:directory-create(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[permissions as element(sec:permission)*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[collections as xs:string*,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[quality as xs:int?,]</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">[forest-ids as xs:unsignedLong*]</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Creates a directory. If security is enabled, the document permissions and collections are set to the given parameters, if supplied. Otherwise, the current user's default permissions and/or collections are applied. If the beginning of the the document URI is protected, the user must have access to that URI privilege. If the directory URI does not end with a '/' one is added. If the directory already exists, then nothing is done. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:directory-create\">Complete Information for xdmp:directory-create</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:document-delete","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:document-delete(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Deletes a document from the database. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:document-delete\">Complete Information for xdmp:document-delete</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:directory-delete","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:directory-delete(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Deletes a directory and its children from the database. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:directory-delete\">Complete Information for xdmp:directory-delete</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:collection-delete","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:collection-delete(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Deletes from the database every document in a collection. If there are no documents in the specified collection, then nothing is deleted, and <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">xdmp:collection-delete</code> still returns the empty sequence. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:collection-delete\">Complete Information for xdmp:collection-delete</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:node-replace","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:node-replace(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">old as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">new as node()</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Replaces a node. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:node-replace\">Complete Information for xdmp:node-replace</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:node-delete","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:node-delete(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">old as node()</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Deletes a node from the database. On-the-fly constructed nodes cannot be deleted. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:node-delete\">Complete Information for xdmp:node-delete</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:node-insert-before","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:node-insert-before(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">sibling as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">new as node()</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Adds an immediately preceding sibling to a node. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:node-insert-before\">Complete Information for xdmp:node-insert-before</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:node-insert-after","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:node-insert-after(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">sibling as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">new as node()</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Adds an immediately following sibling to a node. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:node-insert-after\">Complete Information for xdmp:node-insert-after</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:node-insert-child","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:node-insert-child(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">parent as node(),</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">new as node()</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Adds a new last child to a node. Only element nodes and document nodes can have children. Element nodes cannot have document node children. Document nodes cannot have multiple element node children. On-the-fly constructed nodes cannot be updated. The parameters must specify individual nodes and not node sets. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:node-insert-child\">Complete Information for xdmp:node-insert-child</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:document-add-collections","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:document-add-collections(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">collections as xs:string*</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Adds the named document to the given collections. For each collection that is protected, the user must have permissions to update that collection or have the <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">any-collection</code> privilege. For each unprotected collection, the user must have the <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">unprotected-collections</code> privilege. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:document-add-collections\">Complete Information for xdmp:document-add-collections</a></div></div>");
		fDocs.put("xdmp:document-remove-collections","<div><div style=\"font-family:Courier;\"><div style=\"color:#c00831;\">xdmp:document-remove-collections(</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">uri as xs:string,</div><div style=\"padding-left:2em;\">collections as xs:string*</div><div>)</div></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><apidoc:summary xmlns:apidoc=\"http://marklogic.com/xdmp/apidoc\"> Removes the named document from the given collections. For each collection that is protected, the user must have permissions to update that collection or have the <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">any-collection</code> privilege. For each unprotected collection, the user must have the <code xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">unprotected-collections</code> privilege. </apidoc:summary></div><div style=\"margin-top:1em;\"><a style=\"font-size:.8em\" href=\"mlapidoc:xdmp:document-remove-collections\">Complete Information for xdmp:document-remove-collections</a></div></div>");
